headline: Medtronic Posts Better-Than-Expected Earnings. Here’s Why the Stock Is Falling.
summary: Medical device maker  Medtronic  reported quarterly earnings and net sales that topped consensus views.  Medtronic  on Tuesday posted fiscal third-quarter adjusted earnings of $1.36 a share, narrowly beating analysts’ forecasts of $1.34.  Medtronic’s profit declined from the same period last year on a non-adjusted basis, slipping to $1.14 billion from $1.29 billion.

headline: Truist Securities Reiterates Buy on DexCom, Lowers Price Target to $80
summary: Truist Securities  analyst Richard Newitter   reiterates DexCom (NASDAQ:DXCM) with a Buy and lowers the price target from $82 to $80.
